# React Component Conventions

## File Organization
- Group components by feature: `src/components/guestbook/`, `src/components/puzzles/`, etc.
- Each feature folder has a barrel `index.ts` exporting all components
- Components are `"use client"` unless they only do server-side work

## Naming Convention
- `FeatureList` — main layout component (grid + form + edit modal)
- `FeatureCard` — individual entry card with gradient overlay
- `FeatureForm` — create/add form with controlled inputs
- `FeatureEditModal` — edit modal wrapping `<Modal>` from `@/components/ui/Modal`
- `FeatureDetailsView` — detail/expanded view (used by expenses, loons)
- `FeatureLightbox` — feature-specific lightbox (gallery, puzzles)

## Card Pattern
```tsx
import { CARD_GRADIENTS } from "@/lib/ui-gradients";
<div className="group relative mb-4 break-inside-avoid overflow-hidden rounded-lg border bg-card shadow-sm">
  <div className={`pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 ${CARD_GRADIENTS.emerald}`} />
  <div className="relative p-4">{/* content */}</div>
</div>
```

## Edit/Delete Buttons
- Show on hover with `opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity`
- Edit: only if `isOwned` (or `isOwner`)
- Delete: if `canDelete` (owner or admin)
- Use `ConfirmModal` for delete confirmation

## Form Sidebar Layout
- Desktop: sticky right column `lg:sticky lg:top-6 lg:self-start`
- Grid: `grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[3fr,400px]`
- Mobile: scroll button that jumps to form section

## Masonry Layout
- CSS columns: `columns-1 gap-4 sm:columns-2 lg:columns-3`
- Cards use `break-inside-avoid`

## Tailwind v4 Notes
- Use `bg-linear-to-br` instead of `bg-gradient-to-br`
- Use `aspect-4/3` instead of `aspect-[4/3]`

## Existing Feature Component Sets
Fully built: guestbook, puzzles, blog, gallery, expenses, loons, todos, account
Each has List, Card, Form, EditModal (and some have Lightbox, DetailsView)
